  "factionRules": [
    {
      "name": "Boost Actions",
      "description": "Murderwings are experts in aerial combat, lashing out at flailing prey as they soar overhead on columns of flame. Some actions are known as BOOST actions. These are actions performed during other actions when a BOOST is used. Each operative cannot perform more than one BOOST action per activation/"
    },
    {
      "name": "Astartes",
      "description": "These genetically modified superhumans are made for one purpose: war. During each friendly MURDERWING operative’s activation, it can perform either two Shoot actions or two Fight actions. If it’s two Shoot actions, a bolt pistol must be selected for at least one of them. Each friendly MURDERWING operative can"
    },
    {
      "name": "Commentary",
      "description": "me of the best mobility in the game thanks to their Jump o boost around the killzone, which is similar to flying except above them. A boost allows Murderwing operatives to tives effortlessly, so you can get up onto Vantage terrain, side of a building, or charge down someone hiding behind potential is very powerful. It enables you to reach locations s you the capability to set up fights your opponent can’t. ir success – safely concealing your operatives out of the l within your own. Then you can control the flow of battle, ging when it suits you. the hawkish nature of Chaos Space Marine Raptors, it’s hem. It can be tempting to boost forward as fast as possible erwing aren’t the most durable team, so you could lose Similarly, you’ll miss out on some of the unique tricks the enemy, picking them off and whittling them down. Once ed their nerves, you can close in for the killing blow! Many Boost actions – actions you can do after a boost, usually osted over. The Huntmaster’s Strike From Above action our equipment all deal small but unavoidable damage."
    }
  ],
  "markersTokens": [],
  "strategyPloys": [
    {
      "name": "Murderwing",
      "cpCost": 1,
      "description": "MARKER/TOKEN GUIDE Damnation Warp Points marker Challenge Warp Fuel Token token Vox-casters token"
    },
    {
      "name": "Cull The Weak",
      "cpCost": 1,
      "description": "Opportunistic predators all, the warriors of a Murderwing seek to single out and pick off the most vulnerable prey. Whenever a friendly MURDERWING operative is shooting or fighting, its weapons have the Punishing weapon rule if any of the following are true for the operative that friendly operative is shooting or fighting against: • It’s at least 2\" lower than that friendly operative. • Its APL stat is less than normal. • It was wounded at the start of the activation/counteraction."
    },
    {
      "name": "Predators Above",
      "cpCost": 1,
      "description": "Murderwings excel when striking from above, using their mobility and jet-assisted might to massacre their enemies. Whenever a friendly MURDERWING operative is at least 2\" higher than the killzone floor, its weapons have the Balanced weapon rule. Whenever a friendly MURDERWING operative does a BOOST, its weapons have the Balanced weapon rule until the end of that activation."
    },
    {
      "name": "Nightmare On High",
      "cpCost": 1,
      "description": "So swift and elusive are the Murderwing, that even the most skilled of sharpshooters struggle to hit them as they soar above. Whenever an operative is shooting a friendly MURDERWING operative that’s at least 2\" higher than the killzone floor, or that did a BOOST during this turning point, you can re-roll one of your defence dice."
    },
    {
      "name": "Instil Fear",
      "cpCost": 1,
      "description": "Such is the savagery and horror of the Murderwing, that even the boldest of combatants find their hearts gripped by paralysing fear. Whenever a friendly MURDERWING operative is fighting, Normal Dmg of 3 or more inflicts 1 less damage on it."
    }
  ],
  "firefightPloys": [
    {
      "name": "Wings Of Darkness",
      "cpCost": 1,
      "description": "Warp-corrupted jump packs lend their wearers terrifying speed. MURDERWING operative is performing the Fall Back or Reposition action, when it does a BOOST. That operative can be set up an additional 3\" away during that BOOST (adding this to the permitted move distance), but it cannot perform the Shoot, Fight or Carving Blow (see DEPREDATOR operative) action until the next turning point. You cannot use this ploy during the first turning point."
    }
  ],
  "factionEquipment": [
    {
      "name": "Vox-casters",
      "epCost": 1,
      "description": "Vox-speakers wrought into the panels of corrupted power armour enhance the roar of engines and the animal cries of predatory warriors, overwhelming the senses of stunned prey. Once per turning point, one friendly MURDERWING operative can perform the following unique action: VOX-CRY 1AP Each enemy operative within 3\" of this operative takes a stun test. For an operative to take a stun test, roll one D6: on a 3+, subtract 1 from its APL stat until the end of its next activation. An operative cannot perform this action while it has a Conceal order. NOTES:",
      "restrictions": null
    }
  ]
}